message.content:
Rule Learning, Theory. 

The paper discusses the development and implementation of Mode-Directed Inverse Entailment (MDIE) as a generalization and enhancement of previous approaches for inverting deduction. This involves learning from positive data and inverting implication between pairs of clauses, which falls under the sub-category of Rule Learning. The paper also provides a re-assessment of previous techniques in terms of inverse entailment, which is a theoretical aspect of AI.
